    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSyntax highlighting disappears after `:restart` when using a documented \"temporary session\" way of restarting while preserving current layout.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean -- Makefile` (from the root of this repo, for example)\n2. `mksession! Session.vim | restart source Session.vim` - colors are not shown. Even after `:set termguicolors` they are not shown. Executing `:edit` shows colors again.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nRestarting while saving layout with temporary session works exactly the same as if manually do \"Save session\" - \"Quit\" - \"Start with the same arguments\" - \"Source session\". Including present syntax highlighting.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2727+gad4bc2d90c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.19.10-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1-arch1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
